Name: Negative pH (band)
rawData: Negative pH is an Electronic music band from Oakland, California that formed in 2000. The two band members met through Mp3.com in mid-1999. Joshua Fanene and Micheal Bailey co-write the band's songs  with influences including Nine Inch Nails, Pendulum, Ennio Morricone, Ozzy Osbourne, Pitchshifter, and Aphex Twin. The band has four albums including liminal space, which was self-released in 2004, OVRMND, 201X and 201Y. They have been featured in both local and national publications like Hyperactive Magazine issue #7.
